\c 26
\s1 REMEMBER! At the start of a chapter, you must have a backslash p before backslash v. Usually this follows s1. If you forget to do this, all the text will be the chapter number size. Does this work?
\p
\v 1 Not much later there was a famine in that land, like what had happened in Abraham's time. Because of that, for a while Isaac— with all that he owned, moved to Gerar, that is a district of Abimelek's authority, a Philistine king.
\v 2 Then the LORD showed himself to him and said, "Don't go to Egypt! Remain in the land that I will show to you.
\v 3 Stay in this land as a foreigner, then I will be with you and bless you. I will give all of this area to you and to your descendants. I will fulfill My promise to your father Abraham.
\v 4 I will give you very many descendants— like as many as stars in the sky. I will give all of this area to them, and they will become a blessing for all people groups on earth.
\v 5 I do this because previously your father Abraham
